4.54/5  rDev -1.5%look: 4.5 | smell: 4.75 | taste: 4.5 | feel: 4.25 |  overall: 4.5AngEo, Oct 02, 2016
4.53/5  rDev -1.7%look: 4.75 | smell: 4.25 | taste: 4.5 | feel: 4.75 |  overall: 4.75Service:	Bottle
Best before: 	Jan-6-2019 (bottled Jan-2016)
A:	
Pours a muddy mohagany with an enormous khaki head that is basically sturdy as a dollop of dirty-looking whipped cream.  Great retention; gorgeous lacing.  (4.75)	
S:	
Aromas of musty old barnwood and cherries with a slightly tart twang that is barely perceptible.  (4.25)	
T:	
Waves of smooth earthy, rich, brown bread and workbench dirt, dripping in dark fruit character with a touch of bubblegum and caramelized sugar in the finish. (4.5)	
M:	
Medium+ bodied with active (but soft) carbonation, puffy, fluffy feel, drinkable.  (4.75)	
O:	
Wow.  
This is a very nice, very flavorful, very enjoyable beer.  I am a big fan of Belgians and that is one that I've always wanted to get ahold of.  I'm glad I did (merci, Steve).  A unified sensory experience that highlights the incredible nature of brewing.  Walks a line between big and drinkable, sweet and earthy, rich and refreshing.  This is a world-class beer.  Have it if you ever see it!  (4.75) 1,019 charactersTheDoctor, Oct 02, 2016
