5/5  rDev +8.5%look: 5 | smell: 5 | taste: 5 | feel: 5 |  overall: 5I had this beer as part of a Trappist tasting that my friends and I had been putting together for a while.  Obviously, the guy who brought the Westy 12 didn't have to bring anything else.  We started with it, and split a bottle 4 ways, into traditional chalice type glass.  It's a gorgeous dark dark plum-brown, with a nice little head (pouring left something to be desired, but that's on us).  It smells like you'd expect and hope a quad to smell, and the same holds true for taste and feel.  It wasn't too sweet, wasn't too boozy (considering it's over 10%).  I didn't let it sit on my tongue for too long, but it was incredibly smooth drinking.  Will head to Belgium soon to buy some more. 692 charactersdfd02186, May 10, 2016
