4.69/5  rDev +1.7%look: 4.5 | smell: 4.75 | taste: 4.75 | feel: 4.25 |  overall: 4.75Got to Paris and found my way to a specialty beer store where I ran into this gem. At €20 a pop, it surely is the most expensive beer I have ever purchased. But I mist say, it was worth it. 
Served from bottle into special Westvleteren glass. 
Deep dark red color with frothy head. 
Strong smell, bit boozy with plethora of fruit. 
Rich sweet taste, the booziness comes through a bit as well. Strong, but not overwhelming. Very clean and smooth. 
This beer is worth the hype. If you can find it, snag it. 
Got another bottle that will be aged. 545 charactersArminius757, Jan 11, 2015
5/5  rDev +8.5%look: 5 | smell: 5 | taste: 5 | feel: 5 |  overall: 5weezarc, Jan 11, 2015
