5/5  rDev +8.5%look: 5 | smell: 5 | taste: 5 | feel: 5 |  overall: 5It's really unnecessary for me to review this beer. It's perfect but there are a couple highlights I'd like to share. First of all, the actual bottle itself has some serious weight to it making the iconic bottle an awesome momento and keep sake. 
The other thing that really stood out to me was the taste. I've always stuck to a misplaced stereotype that quads are heavy, but as I've enjoyed better beers in this category I've come to appreciate that they are not heavy at all. This beer has a serious lightness to it that makes it very drinkable, you almost forget to slow down and savor it.
The first time I drank this brew we paid nearly $60/bottle... Thank goodness 4 of us were splitting a six pack. I get it, it's impossible to find and therefore its unavailability is a downside; however I believe this beer is the one exception to the rule based on the duration of time it has held a near perfect rating.
In fact other beers are considered the #1 beer in the world just to keep this beautiful brew out of the top slot very single year. But look it up, it's true, and frankly the monks don't care what we think. We've been lucky to get our hands on quite a stash so my dear friend is cellaring some for 1,3,5, & 7 years.... Should be a good decade. Cheers. 1,266 charactersAbbbp, Jul 17, 2013
