4.21/5  rDev -8.7%look: 4 | smell: 4.25 | taste: 4.25 | feel: 4 |  overall: 4.2511.2 FL OZ bottle
Served in a Westvleteren XII chalice
Bottled 2012
This beer pours a murky brown with some tea colored highlights. It is topped with less than an inch of tan head that some decent lacing.
I get aromas of dates and figs with some molasses. 
The taste is very similar to the smell. I taste dates and figs with hints of molasses and spices. 
Medium mouthfeel with a dry finish.
I am glad that I got to try this beer a couple times in my life. It is not life changing. I prefer St. Bernardus Abt 12 and Rochefort 10 to this. I am not saying it is a bad beer. I like it very much, but I see no reason to chase it when there are better options that are much easier to find. 689 charactersbuschbeer, Feb 18, 2013
