4.08/5  rDev -11.5%look: 4.5 | smell: 4 | taste: 4 | feel: 4.5 |  overall: 4Thanks to MrKennedy for very generously gifting me the bottle. Have been wanting to try this one since soon after I "discovered" craft beer, roughly two years ago.
Bottle dated 07.01.14
Pours a nice black-purple with a very healthy good-looking white head. Nice cloudy lacing.
Smell is lots of yeast and some alcohol. Very very pleasant fresh yeast smell though, almost porridge-like. Some celery. Raisins and grapes.
Taste is also very yeasty with a really nice grapey sweetness which is well balanced with alcohol bitterness. Aftertaste is very alcoholic. Normally I find quads a bit sweet but this one has a really potent and enjoyable bitterness and bite to it.
On the mouthfeel, feels like the beer is laced with oatmeal- thick, creamy and awesome.
Is this beer overrated? I would say yes. It is still excellent however. For something represented as being all things to all people, it holds up well. Can't wait to try the -BA version! 945 charactersdanieelol, Nov 17, 2011
